![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/ca209e1b-38e7-48e3-bb00-d43d058782d6/414a.jpg?format=original)

This week on the Major Issues Podcast, the hosts look ahead to 2026 and make their bold predictions across movies, television, and comics. From potential breakout hits to looming disasters, they dig into upcoming releases, shifting creative trends, and the franchises facing the most pressure in the year ahead.

Which projects are poised to surprise, which ones could stumble, and what might define the next phase of pop culture? It is a forward-looking episode packed with hot takes, informed speculation, and plenty of debate as the hosts try to call their shots before the year begins.

Please leave us a **_review_** on [**ITunes**](https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/major-issues-podcast/id1321720972) so we can grow our audience and grow as podcasters! Rate us wherever podcasts are found. Don't forget to check out our merchandise! All episodes of Major Issues are brought to you by **ComicBook Clique**, the only stop for the latest and greatest things to come to comic books and comic book media.

